A vector space  $ V $  over a field  $  \mathbb{F} $  with
a function  $ V \to \mathbb{F} $ ,  $ x \mapsto |x | $ , the  norm, satisfying
 
   \par
  $  |x | \geq 0 $ 
   \par
  $  | \lambda x |=| \lambda | |x | $ 
   \par
  $  |x+y | \leq  |x |+ |y | $ 
 
for any  $ x,y \in V $  and  $  \lambda  \in  \mathbb{F} $ . We may define a metric by
 $ d(x,y)= |x-y | $  to make  $ V $  into a metric space.


